-- Suspect in Sale of Swiss Tax Data Found Dead in Cell, SF Says
-- B y   P a u l   V e r s c h u u r
-- 2010-10-01T10:57:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/suspect-in-sale-of-swiss-tax-data-found-dead-in-cell-sf-says.html
A man being investigated in
connection with the theft of Swiss bank account details and
their sale to Germany has been found dead in his Swiss prison
cell, SF television reported, citing the prosecution.  The 42-year-old’s body was found early yesterday, according
to the report, which quoted prosecution spokeswoman Jeanette
Balmer. The circumstances surrounding his death aren’t clear
yet, SF said on its website, adding there were no indications of
any third-party involvement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Verschuur at 
 pverschuur@bloomberg.net  